<br>
Cap: ac2, sta1, int1, mana5<br>
Sandals: ac3, cha2, int1, mana10<br>
Sleeves: ac3, int1, agi1, mana5<br>
Robe: ac5, int2, agi2, mana10<br>
Gloves: ac2, dex2, int1, mana5<br>
Trousers: ac4, sta2, int2, mana5<br>
Bracers (x2): ac1, dex2, int1, mana3<br>
<br>
A couple clues to help the young wiz get started...<br>
<br>
When asking to begin each part do not add an S to the end of the item type (&quot;I want to craft bracer&quot;, &quot;...trouser&quot;, &quot;...sleeve&quot;, etc.)<br>
<br>
A component needed for the pants is a &quot;runaway clock motor&quot;. It doesnt come from a runaway clock, it drops from a Rebel Clockwork (found by the Minotaur cave).<br>
<br>
Small cloth components wont work for these parts. Run to the tailor in Felwithe or hunt in CB for the cloth components ( why small parts wont work is kind of odd...).<br>
<br>
The staff needed for the robe is dropped by a 13th(?) level necro (the evil Faeronoliop). The others around him do not assist, but still use caution. My lil 15th wiz got him fairly easy, but I still took considerable damage.<br>
<br>
Enjoy!<br>
